The paper proposes a model for graph generation through reinforcement learning, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The specific application domain is molecular graph generation, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. The model incorporates domain-specific rules, which suggests the involvement of structured information (cs.SI).
